Summary:¶

  • The data is obtained from server NTXD1155, ACT_FASTFLOW database and view vw_bcp_quotes_flat.
  • Filtering for only the data after the year 2016 we have 54169 data points with 342 columns.
  • Considering the first submission date, there's a significant increase in the count of quotes from 2016 to 2017.
  • The conversion count over the years 2016 and 2017 has been more or less the same, whereas the number of quotes has seen an increase from 2016 to 2017 which is evident from the previous graph. Therefore, the conversion rate has seen an approx. dip of 2%
  • 310 columns have atleast one or the other null values.
  • More than 200 columns have 85% null values.
  • There are 15 columns with 100% null values.
  • Dropped the column "Key Information"as it contains text characters.
  • There are 826 unique brokers.
  • Grouping by broker along with quote count shows us that, most brokers have around 65 quotes.
  • Top 3 Brokers by quote count: Allianz Business Services Ltd. Arthur J Gallagher Swinton Business
  • Hughes Insurance stands out to be the top Broker by quote count and conversion rate.
  • Majority of the brokers refer a quote on an average about 2 times.
  • The tipping point is 3 which essentially hints at the fact that after 3 referrals the conversion rate is not significant and reaches a saturation point.
  • Grouping by Vehicle count: If we look at the conversion rate, vehicle count of 15 has a higher conversion rate, whereas if we take a closer look at the data, vehicle count of 15 has lesser data points as compared to vehicle count of 1 which stands out with approx. 11k quote keys and 777 conversions.
  • Grouping by converted: Average number of vehicles which gets converted is between 1 - 2 Evident from the data is that on an average, double the number of times referred, better is the chance of a conversion. Average number of submissions is almost triple that for non converted quotes.
  • Grouping by Status of Entity doesn't give much detail about conversion rates as most of them tend to be arounf 7 - 8 %
  • The most frequently quoted premium values in GBP are in the range of 1,00,000 to 10,00,000.

    first_submission_year=bcp['First Submission Date'].dt.year
)

    'Quote Key': 'count'
}).reset_index()
ax = sns.barplot(x='first_submission_year', y='Quote Key', data=group_by_year)
_ = ax.set(xlabel='First Submission Year', ylabel='Frequency', title='Count of quotes per year')

Conversion rate per year¶

conversion_per_year = bcp.groupby('first_submission_year').agg({

    'Quote Key': 'count'
}).reset_index()

conversion_per_year = conversion_per_year.assign(
